        "@value": "Screes come to be through physical disintegration of geological formations and are the result of becoming smaller and smaller along time. They are accumulated on site due to sedimentary processes or human activity. Further subdivision is made according to their particle size and constellation."
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Schutt und Sand: Lockersedimente wie Schuttfluren, GerÃ¶llfelder, SchotterflÃ¤chen und sandige Bereiche bis hin zu GerÃ¶ll (bis ca. max. 2 m Durchmesser) ohne erkennbare Beimischung von Humus. Der Vegetationsanteil betrÃ¤gt maximal 10%."
